Confluence supports anonymous access to pages, but when they are linked to JIRA issues, and a user that doesn't have access to Confluence logs into JIRA and sees the link, it appears as though the user doesn't have access to the page.  However, we have Anonymous access turned on for a lot of our spaces so that anyone in our company can view the pages.  The Application link from JIRA for those links should fall back to an Anonymous access attempt to display the link to the wiki page if the initial login attempt fails.  This would greatly improve the useability of the systems.

Another option is to change the behavior of setting up multiple authentication types on an Application link so that if the first primary method is denied access, then it will attempt each subsequent access type to attempt to read the appropriate data.

Please vote.  Thanks.

